QUALITY-HUB: sistema modular que monitorea en tiempo real la calidad y nivel del aguas subterraáneas y superficiales

18.description:
In Chile, an average of CLP $20 billion is spent each year on water scarcity. Even so, today 1.4 million people do not have access to drinking water. According to the CASEN survey, conducted in 2017. With all this, Chile appears as 1 among the 30 countries with the highest water risk in the world for the year 2025.

Of the sources of this resource, which are; Surface water, glaciers and groundwater, it is of the latter that we have less information and control. And also, this is our main savings account, since in the event of a decrease in surface water, it is necessary to migrate and make use of groundwater.

Several initiatives have been carried out to establish possible water scenarios in the near future, seeking water sustainability. To achieve this, it is necessary to have updated information on the water situation in our country.

That is why we have developed QUALITY-HUB to contribute to the control of the use of this resource.

This is a modular system for monitoring the dynamic level and quality of water in wells used for groundwater collection, allowing to know in real time its condition. In it, 3 fundamental characteristics are recognized; Control, follow-up and visualization, helping our clients to be able to carry out more finished water and asset management planning, providing them with all the information they require.

Una vez que las empresas B, fundaciones, club deportivos o lideres de comunidades activen un EcoDesafío con propósito y agreguen productos a la EcoVitrina. 
Los usuarios regeneradores podrán completar los retos y ganar recompensas OPIS para canjear por bienes y servicios EcoAmigables.
